Code-
var compose = function(functions) {
    return function(x) {
        let result = x;

        for (let i = functions.length - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
            result = functions[i](result);
        }

        return result;
    };
};



Function Composition-
Problem-
Given:
functions → array of functions [f1, f2, ..., fn]

Return a new function:

fn(x) = f1(f2(f3(...fn(x))))

If array is empty → return identity function:

f(x) = x

Logic-
Return a function that takes x
Start from the last function (right to left)
Apply each function on the result of the previous one
Return final value
